  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, then boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces, then add them to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and reserve the pot</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720536478947-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720536478947-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720536478947-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720536478947-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1720536478947-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>natural</strong> <strong>yoghurt</strong> and most of your <strong>curry powder</strong> to a large bowl (you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Add your <strong>ground paprika</strong> and <strong>garam masala </strong>with<strong> </strong>a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>Tandoori-style marinade</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720536481677-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720536481677-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720536481677-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720536481677-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1720536481677-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> chicken breast strips </strong>to the <strong>Tandoori-style marinade</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until the chicken is completely coated – this is your <strong>marinated chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720536486296-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720536486296-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720536486296-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720536486296-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1720536486296-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick), over a medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>marinated chicken breast strips</strong> and cook for 6-7 min on each side until lightly charred and cooked through (no pink meat!) – these are your <strong>Tandoori-style chicken strips</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4 or more? Use 2 pans!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1720536490733-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1720536490733-x400.jpg",
