            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your<strong> cucumber[s]</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into thin wedges</p><p>Top, tail and coarsely grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>into wedges</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720536493944-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720536493944-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720536493944-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720536493944-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1720536493944-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> grated carrot</strong> to a bowl<strong> </strong>with the<strong> chopped cucumber </strong>and <strong>tomato wedges</strong></p><p>Add a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>zingy salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720536497385-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720536497385-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720536497385-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720536497385-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1720536497385-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are cooked, add a knob of<strong> butter</strong> to the reserved pot with your <strong>black mustard seeds</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>remaining curry powder</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook over a medium heat for 30 secs or until the butter has melted and the spices are fragrant, then add the <strong>cooked potatoes</strong> to the pot</p><p>Stir it all together and cook for a final 1 min or until fragrant and the potatoes are well coated – these are your <strong>curried potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720536500643-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720536500643-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720536500643-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720536500643-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1720536500643-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Tandoori-style chicken strips</strong> with the <strong>curried potatoes</strong> and <strong>zingy salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Add the <strong>remaining natural yoghurt</strong> and your <strong>mango chutney</strong> to the side</p><p>Top with your <strong>crispy onions</strong> and garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
